## Full Information Lifecycle Control Summary

| Lifecycle Phase | Primary Risk | Key Controls | NIST SP 800-53 Families |
|---|---|---|---|
| Creation | Input errors; transmission security; over-collection | TLS; input validation; minimum necessary; staff training | SC, SA, AT |
| Active Use | Unauthorized access; privilege creep; integrity | RBAC; MFA; session timeout; audit logging; access reviews | AC, AU, IA |
| Storage | Backup security; retention compliance; key management | RDS/S3 encryption; access control; retention policy; KMS | MP, SC, CP |
| Archival | Out of sight risk; format obsolescence; key lifecycle | Equivalent controls; format standards; key management continuity | MP, SC, CP |
| Disposal | Incomplete purge; backup persistence; key destruction | Cryptographic erasure; disposal log; backup coordination | MP, AU |

